In 1981, six years after joining Fleetwood Mac, Stevie Nicks went solo for the first time with her debut album ‚ÄòBella Donna‚Äô. A massive success, it sold more than five million copies in the U.S., topped the album charts and produced four hit singles, including her signature anthem, "Edge Of Seventeen." More platinum albums followed ‚Äì ‚ÄòThe Wild Heart‚Äô (1983), ‚ÄòRock A Little‚Äô (1985), and ‚ÄòThe Other Side Of The Mirror‚Äô (1989).

In 2019, Stevie Nicks made history by becoming the first female artist inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame twice - first as a member of Fleetwood Mac in 1998, and most recently in recognition of an extraordinary solo career that spans nearly 40 years.

title: We Went On 7 Dates In 7 Decades
description:
Thanks to Olay for sponsoring us & helping make this video come to life! You can check out Olay‚Äôs new cleansing melts here: https://www.Olay.com/CleansingMelts #ad

So as some of you guys might know, I am a bit of a historical fashion nerd - over the years, we‚Äôve done a number of decade fashion videos about the 50s, 60s, 70s, 80s, 90s, *and* 00s, we‚Äôve tried on vintage wedding dresses, and we have even gotten a full 18th century Colonial Williamsburg makeover.

And whenever we go on these little journeys to the past, it‚Äôs always really fun when we‚Äôre able to have Tyler dress up as well to explore the decades with me (his 1980s Flock of Eagles haircut still comes to me in the sweetest of dreams).

So we decided to go full couples historical makeover - and do a whole video of them! So while we were in Los Angeles a few weeks ago, we got 7 head-to-toe historical makeovers (with hair, makeup, and outfits, oh my) and went on 7 historically accurate dates!

Which decade was your favorite? Did Tyler and I pull off the looks? What era should we travel to next?

title: What If The Universe DID NOT Start With The Big Bang?
description:

Check out the Space Time Merch Store
https://www.pbsspacetime.com/shop

Here‚Äôs the story we like to tell about the beginning of the universe. Space is expanding evenly everywhere, but if you rewind that expansion you find that  all of space was once compacted in an infinitesimal point of infinite density‚Äîthe singularity at the beginning of time. The expansion of the universe from this point is called the Big Bang.  We like to tell this story because it's the correct conclusion from the description of an expanding universe that followed Einstein's general theory of relativity back in the 19-teens. But since then we've learned so much more since then. Does our modern understanding of the universe still insist on a point-like Big Bang? Recent work actually gives us a way to avoid the beginning of time.

title: Dream Productions | Available December 11 on Disney+
description:
From the world of Inside Out comes #DreamProductions üé• available December 11 and in 2025 comes #WinOrLose ü•é available February 19, only on Disney+.

ABOUT ‚ÄúDREAM PRODUCTIONS‚Äù
Taking place in between the events of ‚ÄúInside Out‚Äù and ‚ÄúInside Out 2,‚Äù ‚ÄúDream Productions‚Äù is an all-new series about the studio inside Riley‚Äôs mind where dreams really do come true‚Äîevery night, on time and on budget. Riley is growing up and when her memories need some extra processing, Joy and the rest of the Core Emotions send them to Dream Productions. Acclaimed director Paula Persimmon (voice of Paula Pell) faces a nightmare of her own: Trying to create the next hit dream after being paired up with Xeni (voice of Richard Ayoade), a smug daydream director looking to step up into the big leagues of night dreams. Also featuring the voices of Amy Poehler, Maya Rudolph, Ally Maki, Kensington Tallman, Liza Lapira, Tony Hale, Lewis Black and Phyllis Smith, the hilarious, mockumentary-style series is written and directed by Mike Jones and produced by Jaclyn Simon.

Christina‚Äôs intention with rerecording & performing these select tracks was to pay homage to the music in a way that honors the girl she was 25 years ago while remaining authentic to the woman she is today.
